import React, {useState} from 'react'
import {Form, Label, FormText, FormGroup, Input,  Button} from "reactstrap"

const FormElements = () =>  {
        // UseState Hook that defines our database collection and take its value also control
        const {inputData, setInputData} = useState({
            creator:"", title:"", message:"", tags:"", selectedFile:""
        })




    return (
        <Form className="w-50">
        <FormGroup>
        <FormText color="light">
            Share your short impression
        </FormText>
      </FormGroup>
      <FormGroup>
        <Label for="creator">Creator</Label>
        <Input type="text" name="email" id="creator" placeholder="type your name..." />
      </FormGroup>
      <FormGroup>
        <Label for="title">Title</Label>
        <Input type="text" name="title" id="title" placeholder="title..." />
      </FormGroup>
      <FormGroup>
        <Label for="title">Message</Label>
        <Input type="text" name="title" id="message" placeholder="your message..." />
      </FormGroup>
      <FormGroup>
        <Label for="title">Tags</Label>
        <Input type="text" name="title" id="tags" placeholder="to your friends" />
      </FormGroup>
      <FormGroup>
        <Label for="text">Your impression</Label>
        <Input type="textarea" name="text" id="text" placeholder="share your impression" />
      </FormGroup>
      <Button type="submit">Submit</Button>
    </Form>
    )
}

export default FormElements
